## Part 7 — Drawables to create

**`res/drawable/gradient_card_scrim.xml`**
```xml
<shape>
  <gradient
    android:type="linear"
    android:angle="90"
    android:startColor="#00000000"
    android:centerColor="#80000000"
    android:endColor="#E0000000" />
</shape>
```
This fades from transparent at the top to near-black at the bottom of the
cover art so the title text is always readable regardless of the game art.

**`res/drawable/bg_icon_pill.xml`**
```xml
<ripple android:color="@color/gn_accent_subtle">
  <item android:id="@android:id/mask">
    <shape android:shape="oval"><solid android:color="#FFFFFFFF"/></shape>
  </item>
  <item>
    <shape android:shape="oval"><solid android:color="#66000000"/></shape>
  </item>
</ripple>
```
Used as the background for icon buttons overlaid on cover art (favorite, etc.).
The semi-transparent dark pill keeps the icon readable on any art color.
